---
// Problem section explaining what RootSpec solves
---

<section data-test="problem-section" class="py-16 bg-gray-50 dark:bg-gray-800">
  <div class="container mx-auto px-4 max-w-4xl">
    <h3 class="text-3xl font-bold text-center mb-12">The Problem with Traditional Specs</h3>

    <div data-test="problem-content" class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-8">
      <div class="space-y-6">
        <div class="p-6 bg-white dark:bg-gray-700 rounded-lg shadow">
          <h4 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-3 text-red-600 dark:text-red-400">Spec Drift</h4>
          <p class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-300">
            Documentation becomes outdated as implementation evolves,
            leading to confusion and inconsistency between what's written and what's built.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="p-6 bg-white dark:bg-gray-700 rounded-lg shadow">
          <h4 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-3 text-red-600 dark:text-red-400">Unclear Boundaries</h4>
          <p class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-300">
            Without clear separation between philosophy, requirements, and implementation details,
            teams struggle to know what decisions are fundamental vs. tactical.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="space-y-6">
        <div class="p-6 bg-white dark:bg-gray-700 rounded-lg shadow">
          <h4 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-3 text-red-600 dark:text-red-400">Implementation Gaps</h4>
          <p class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-300">
            Vague requirements lead to interpretation differences,
            causing rework and misaligned expectations between stakeholders.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="p-6 bg-white dark:bg-gray-700 rounded-lg shadow">
          <h4 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-3 text-red-600 dark:text-red-400">Testing Disconnection</h4>
          <p class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-300">
            Tests don't directly validate the original intent,
            making it hard to verify if the implementation truly meets the vision.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>